#
# One project-relative path per line. `#` comments and blank lines are ignored. Read by
# cleanup_orphans() in fkit-claude-init.sh, which deletes each entry — once, announced, per project.
#
# ⛔ THIS LIST IS EXHAUSTIVE BY OWNER RULING (task 36), NOT BY CONVENIENCE.
#    Adding a line here is a NEW OWNER DECISION — it is an `rm -rf` in someone else's project with no
#    rollback. It is the only destructive operation in fkit. Do not add a path because it looks dead.
#
# ⚠️ NEVER add .fkit/settings. It is LIVE ADR-010 lockdown state, rewritten on every launch by
#    build_settings() in fkit-claude.sh. Revision 1 of the migration report listed it for deletion and
#    was wrong; a reviewer trusting that table would have shipped a delete of live state. The
#    reference-check gate in cleanup_orphans() exists to catch exactly that class of mistake: an entry
#    that is still referenced anywhere in claude/ is REFUSED, not deleted. The gate is a backstop for
#    this list, not a substitute for reading it.
#
# Also never targets, for the record: .fkit/intake.md (the owner's hand-typed answers), .fkit/interview,
